      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SOLO SAPPHIRE (1) made an encouraging debut at Cranbourne on Sunday, coming from a much wider barrier for fourth. Open to natural improvement and is better served by the ace draw. THE PASO DOBLE (6) is a colt by What The Hill on debut for the Ryan stable. Readied with a series of trials, winning the latest hitout at Maryborough. That should have him ready to go. Tricky draw for NEDZA THRILLER (13) but he has been racing well, recording back-to-back placings in maiden races before a last-start fourth at this venue. MOSLEY (2) is a mare by Majestic Son making her first appearance for Anne-Maree Conroy. Runner-up in her latest trial at Maryborough. Look for a good showing. ARIVADERCHI (4) is a long-time maiden who draws wider than when runner-up at Bendigo last start but that was his third placing on the trot so he deserves respect.",
